listings.neighborhood_overview: Bloomsbury is such a peaceful, friendly, charming and culturally rich location in London, that it doesn't come as a surprise that the likes of Charles Dickens, Bob Marley, Vera Brittain, Virgina Wolf, Charles Darwin, Ricky Gervais, Dorothy L. Sayers (and her main female character Harriet Vane), Catherine Tate, William Butler Yeats and so many more have lived in the neighbourhood at some point in their lives. We have amazing restaurants, pubs, cafes, cake shops (Bea's of Bloomsbury famous cupcakes are a must!), famous book shops, quirky shops, artistic spaces and workshops (check out Cockpit Yard), parks (Coram's Fields, where adults are welcome only accompanied by a child, is a gem for the little ones entertainment and your peace of mind), the diamond district (Hatton Garden), organic food shops, post office, banks, currency exchange, museums (Dickens' House and the Foundling Museum are a great stop, as well as the British Museum of course), Curzon Cinema (a destination for true cineph
listings.notes: If you fancy a comfortable, safe, quiet, clean and beautiful place to stay, welcome to Merino Hospitality! We ask one thing of you: please be honest in your communications with us, and be aware that PARTIES are NOT WELCOME. We do promote social gatherings to celebrate special occasions, family reunions, corporate meetings and other civilised and decent encounters as one would have at their own homes, but if your plan involves loud music, drunk juvenile behaviour, drug abuse and whatever else floats your boat, do yourself a favour and book a suitable venue for the occasion. We have security and misbehaviour is not tolerated. We request an original and valid form of ID to be presented at the time of arrival. We are selective of our guests and we strive to maintain a good relationship with our neighbours and local community, so the more information you can give us at the time of your enquiry, the better. We apologise in advance if you were to feel offended, but we will ask you for informa
listings.transit: Transportation links are superb, with the Piccadilly line only 2 minutes away and many buses to all corners of the city just around the corner, but you will soon discover that you can walk (yes, you actually can!) everywhere from here. You can be by the river in less than 20 minutes, at the Southbank Centre and National Theatre. Covent Garden, Soho, Chinatown, Theatreland, Leicester Square, Oxford Street Piccadilly Circus, Clerkenwell, St. Paul's Cathedral, The City, Hatton Garden... between 5-20 minutes walking. (20 minutes to St. Paul's. All the others are a 10-minute walk) Feel like stretching it? Ok... in 30 minutes you are by the Houses of Parliament and Big Ben. Another 10 minutes and you got to the Tate! Don't fancy walking and don't like the chaos of public transport? Fine... a cab to any of the places above should cost you no more than £10-£20, depending on traffic. To put it into perspective, buses and the tube cost £1.50 with a cap at £4.40/day. Ah! The cab fare above is for
listings.access: You will have exclusive access to the entire property and all of its facilities. Check-in time is at 3pm and Check-out at 11am as standard. Early check-in and late check-out may be possible depending on availability, and further charges may incur.
listings.interaction: We love welcoming people to London and we are at your disposal for anything you need!  You will be met at the property upon arrival, where you will receive 3 sets of high-security keys and we will go through the features of your home to help you familiarise yourself with your address in London. We will also assist you with any arrangements you may require, and we have extensive knowledge of the local area so feel free to ask anything you want to know. Our interaction can be as much or as little as you wish it to be, but we do like to make friends so if you allow us we would love to invite you for a pint at one of our favourite local pubs.  You will have direct access to our phone lines and email addresses, and our office is just around the corner too so we can always be with you in no time during your stay if you need anything.
listings.house_rules: Mi Casa, Su Casa. And it is your responsibility to maintain OUR casa in a clean and tidy fashion, as you would expect someone to do at your own. Smoking is not allowed and a minimum penalty of £250/night will incur if you choose to ignore this rule. If you are a smoker, please do so outside, and please make sure not to litter our streets; Pets are not allowed, except for guide dogs; We would very much appreciate if you could please empty the fridge, set the dishwasher and clear any rubbish prior to your departure; The landline telephone is complimentary to contact your hosts and to receive calls; other calls will be charged at a 30% markup price; While you are a guest in our properties they are to be kept clean and tidy. listings.host_about:
Founded by husband and wife team Caio and Louise Merino, Merino Hospitality was conceived to fulfill the growing demand of worldwide travellers for an alternative accommodation to the standard hotel room. Our aspiration to provide guests with a unique experience whilst visiting London combined with industry experience, business acumen and ambition led us to create this new venture. We will provide fully serviced accommodation in unique properties that appeal to both corporate and holiday travellers alike.
Each property that we manage is cherry picked for its living space, location and character and are all uniquely designed and furnished and equipped with modern boutique comforts and amenities. In addition, Merino Hospitality will provide bespoke concierge services. Your luxury stay made better!
Your convenience, comfort and satisfaction are pinnacle to us and we are here to ensure that all your requirements are fulfilled during your time in London.
Please get in touch and let's talk through your next visit and let us show you that we have your new address in London.

listings.host_about:
Hi, my husband Philip and I have lived and worked in North London since leaving University.  I work in television and Philip works in music. We have two boys aged 5 and 2.  We really love this area - it's a family friendly community and we have lovely neighbours with children of similar ages.  We are a short walk from 2 lovely parks and lots of cafes, bars and resturants. Crouch End, Highgate and Hampstead are within easy reach. And we are close to brilliant transport links.  It's especially easy and very quick to get to Kings Cross St Pancras and into the West End. 
We often go to Wales during school holidays to visit family and friends and we're happy for people to stay in our house while we're away. 
We love our house and have been slowly but surely renovating it.  We hope you love it too!

listings.neighborhood_overview: Stoke Newington is a friendly, bohemian place with a "village" feel about it. There are lots of independent shops, cafes and restaurants within a few minutes walk of the house. The area is famous for art, food, music and the local restaurants are particularly good.  There is also a lovely park a few minutes walk from our house (Clissold Park).
listings.transit: Buses are the best way to travel from our home, the number 73 & 476 buses run frequently into the west end of London. Angel tube takes about 10-15 minutes to get to on the 73 or 476 which run every 2-3 minutes. Alternatively, the overground is about a 10 minute walk away with trains straight into Liverpool street.
listings.access: You will have access to the whole house, including living room, dining room, kitchen and garden. Feel free to use our washer and dryer, which is extremely rare for London. We do ask you donate 1 pound for each use, as the electricity and water are expensive.
listings.interaction: We are a pretty chilled out couple and will interact as much as you want to. We love to welcome our guests personally and a key will be provided for your stay so you can come and go as you please. Guests are more than welcome to use all of the facilities in the kitchen. We love to meet new people and are here to answer any of your questions about London and make suggestions for hidden gems both locally and throughout London.  As busy professionals, we do value a level of privacy and in the evening like to keep our main living area (living room) as our private space. Guests are welcome to use the whole house during the day and the top floor, double bedroom has lots of space to relax in (DVD, free wifi, large desk area etc)
listings.house_rules: Guests are welcome to use the kitchen and the dining table for their meals but we do like to have our privacy within the living room in the evenings.  Extra guests are not allowed in under any circumstances apart from the people who are listed as staying. We would be grateful if guests could remove their shoes when going upstairs. Check-in / Check-out  Check-In and Check-Out times can be very flexible but just need to be agreed before the beginning of your stay, just to make sure one of us is at home to greet you and say goodbye Check-in/out time is totally flexible and just needs to be agreed in advance. listings.neighborhood_overview: The house is a short walk from Victoria Park Village, a very buzzy diverse/progressive and picturesque area with great restaurants, cafes, delis, Ginger Pig butcher, bars and cosy local pubs doing tasty Sunday lunches. Well Street Common in front of our house joins directly with Victoria Park, great for long walks, sports and a picturesque lake side café. The park is by a canal which runs along to Islington and Camden Town in one direction and to Stratford and the Olympic Village in the other.  East London provides a number of weekend markets, most of which are walking distance from the house including: Broadway Market, Columbia Road Flower Market, Spitalfields, Brick Lane. Entertainment is also close by including Hackney Empire, Hackney Picturehouse, London Fields Lido, boating on the lake in Victoria Park and plenty of gyms and fitness classes in and around the park. A variety of festivals take place in the park throughout Summer.
listings.notes: Pay as you go parking is available outside the house from 10am-midday. Parking otherwise is free.
listings.transit: The area is well serviced by a number of bus and tube options. Our nearest station is Mile End (Central, District, Hammersmith & City lines) a short bus ride from the house and we're also walking distance from Homerton and Hackney Central overland stations. The West End can be accessed in 25 mins. Canary Wharf is a 20 minute bus ride from our house.
listings.access: The kitchen is available for refreshments only. Use of it for cooking will be considered depending on length of stay. As will use of the washing machine and tumble dryer. The house is no smoking but you are welcome to smoke in the garden. All living areas are accessible to guests (excluding the other bedrooms), however we would request that guests respect our privacy in the sitting room at times we are home during an evening or working from home. We can discuss this at the time of booking. If we are out or away then guests may use the sitting room at their leisure.
listings.interaction: If we are at home during your stay, we will be available to assist you and to answer any questions that you have about your stay and the area but will mainly keep to ourselves other times. If away, you will be met by a friend of ours who lives locally. Of course if we are away, which is quite probable while you're staying, then dog and baby will also be away. Our baby is six months old and sleeps in her own nursery next to our room. She is a happy content little thing and sleeps through the night. Of course, as with all babies, there are occasional tears but these are usually fairly short lived. Oskar the dog is a small king charles spaniel x terrier and has an easy going temperament, is well trained and well behaved. He will interact playfully and enthusiastically with anyone who would like to be his friend. If you do not want him visiting your room then please keep the door closed.
